channel.title: Problem with compiling after positions changed
channel.description:
when i try to compile after changing positions like admins or mods on my 508 server it has a few errors
1st it sometimes says
The system cannot find the path specified. Press any key to continue . . .
for the edit on that i have
@echo off cd ../src "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_07\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/io/*.java pause
and then when i change that to the path and the classpath of what java i have it has this error
'"C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_10\bin\javac.exe"' is not recognized as an inte rnal or external command, operable program or batch file. Press any key to continue . . .
and for the edit i have
@echo off cd ../src "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_10\bin\javac.exe" -cp . -d ../bin/ ./palidino76/rs2/io/*.java pause
Thanks for any one who will help me this will be gratley appreciated :)
